@startuml class_diagram_calculator

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor Black
}

class Calculator {
    + add(a, b) : int|float
    + subtract(a, b) : int|float
    + multiply(a, b) : int|float
    + divide(a, b) : int|float
    + factorial(n) : int
    + square(x) : int|float
    + cube(x) : int|float
    + square_root(x) : float
    + cube_root(x) : float
    + power(base, exp) : int|float
    + log10(x) : float
    + ln(x) : float
}

note right of Calculator
  divide()     raises ZeroDivisionError
  factorial()  raises ValueError (negative / non-int)
  square_root() raises ValueError (negative)
  power()      raises ValueError (negative base + non-int exp)
  log10()      raises ValueError (non-positive)
  ln()         raises ValueError (non-positive)
end note

class "__main__ module" as Main {
    + cli_mode() : void
    + main() : void
    ~ _build_registry(calculator) : dict
    ~ _parse_number(raw) : int|float
    ~ _parse_cli_arguments(registry) : tuple|None
    ~ _execute_cli_mode(operation, operands, registry) : void
    ~ _run_interactive_loop(registry) : void  <<MODIFIED>>
}

note bottom of Main
  _run_interactive_loop() now tracks
  consecutive_failures: int (resets on
  success; exits after 3 failures)
end note

Main --> Calculator : creates & calls methods
Main ..> Calculator : via registry dispatch

@enduml
